communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Washington Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

I am requesting a document or documents that list the private companies that receive a copy of the FBI's Terrorist Screening Dataset (TSDS).  In the court case, Elhady v. Kable, No. 20-1119 (4th Cir. 2021), the FBI and DOJ stated that as many as 1,400 corporations received the updated TSDS on a regular basis.  Please provide a document or documents that list these corporations by name.  This list is distributed through the National Crime Information Center (NCIC), so this is information that is readily available.  There may also be private companies that receive the updated TSDS through eGuardian or iGuardian.  Please provide a document or documents that are current as of April 2023.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Winter Calvert

Sincerely,

Winter Calvert

title: Lotus Lounge, 4902 Farragut Road, BK NY

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the New York Freedom of Information Law, I hereby request the following records:

Copies of all enforcement actions taken, letters and memos regarding, or complaints made about the "Lotus Lounge", located at 4902 Farragut Road in Brooklyn, New York.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Gwynne Hogan
